# SEO Implementation Standards

This rule defines the SEO implementation standards for the project to improve visibility and ranking on search engines.

## Metadata Implementation

- Every page must have unique title and description tags
- Use structured data markup (JSON-LD) for rich snippets
- Include Open Graph and Twitter Card metadata for social sharing

## Content Structure

- Use semantic HTML5 elements (header, nav, main, footer)
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (H1-H6)
- Optimize images with descriptive alt text

## Technical SEO

- Ensure fast page load times (under 2 seconds)
- Implement server-side rendering for better indexing
- Use canonical URLs to avoid duplicate content issues

## Keyword Optimization

- Conduct keyword research for target audience
- Place primary keywords in title, H1, and first paragraph
- Maintain keyword density between 1-2%

## Mobile Optimization

- Ensure responsive design across all devices
- Optimize for mobile-first indexing

## Schema Markup

- Implement schema.org markup for relevant content types
- Use local business schema for location-based pages

